{"word":"G3784 - ὀφείλω - opheílō - of-i'-lo - Behove","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ὀφείλω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>opheílō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>of-i'-lo"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Behove"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"வினைச்சொல் - கடன்படு"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"to owe"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Verb / வினைச்சொல்</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> Including its prolonged form (second form) used in certain tenses. Probably from the base of <a href=\"#/G3786 - ὄφελος - óphelos - of'-el-os/3786\">G3786</a> (through the idea of <i>accruing</i>); to <i>owe</i> (pecuniarily); figuratively to <i>be under obligation</i> (<i>ought</i>, <i>must</i>, <i>should</i>); morally to <i>fail</i> in duty: - behove, be bound, (be) debt (-or), (be) due (-ty), be guilty (indebted), (must) need (-s), ought, owe, should. See also <a href=\"#/G3785 - ὄφελον - óphelon - of'-el-on/3785\">G3785</a>."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3781 - ὀφειλέτης - opheilétēs - of-i-let'-ace/3781\">G3781</a>, <a href=\"#/G3782 - ὀφειλή - opheilḗ - of-i-lay'/3782\">G3782</a>, <a href=\"#/G3783 - ὀφείλημα - opheílēma - of-i'-lay-mah/3783\">G3783</a>, <a href=\"#/G3784 - ὀφείλω - opheílō - of-i'-lo/3784\">G3784</a>"}]}